{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1991 |Team=Texas A&M Aggies |Image= |ImageSize= |Conference=Southwest Conference |Division= |ShortConference=SWC |CoachRank=13 |APRank=12 |Record=10-2 |ConfRecord=8-0 |HeadCoach=[[R.C. Slocum]] |StadiumArena=[[Kyle Field]] |Champion= [[Southwest Conference]] Champions |BowlTourney= {{alternate links|1992 Cotton Bowl Classic|Cotton Bowl Classic|title=Cotton Bowl Classic}} vs. [[1991 Florida State Seminoles football team|Florida State]] |BowlTourneyResult= Lost 10-2 }} {{1991 Southwest Conference football standings}} The '''1991 [[Texas A&M Aggies]] football team''' completed the season with a 10-2 record. The Aggies had a regular season [[Southwest Conference]] record of 8-0 and were conference champions. They ended the season with a 2-10 loss in the 1992 [[Cotton Bowl Classic|Cotton Bowl]] to [[1991 Florida State Seminoles football team|Florida State]].
